"From the Latin form of the Greek name <i>Alexandros</i>, from <i>alexein</i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Alexander Copledike was born about 1185, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Joan."},"et":{"Abt 1185–":"umbes 1185–Surnud","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1190":"1190","Abt 1185":"umbes 1185","1235":"1235","1185":"1185","Abt 1209":"umbes 1209","1209":"1209","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1185–":"noin 1185–Kuollut","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1190":"1190","Abt 1185":"noin 1185","1235":"1235","1185":"1185","Abt 1209":"noin 1209","1209":"1209","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1185–":"environ 1185–Décédé","1190–Female":"1190–Décédée","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1185–Male":"1185–Décédé","1190":"1190","Abt 1185":"environ 1185","1235":"1235","1185":"1185","Abt 1209":"environ 1209","1209":"1209","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Alexander Copledike est né environ 1185, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan."},"de":{"Abt 1185–":"um 1185–Verstorben","1190–Female":"1190–Verstorben","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1185–Male":"